title: kama_(third_ascension)_(fate)
body:
[[Kama (fate)|]] in her Third Ascension outfit from [[Fate/Grand Order]]. She is in her young adult form here, having long hair and a pink bow tied to the left side of her head like [[Matou Sakura]]. She [[revealing clothes|only wears]] gold shoulder pads with a purple cape attached to them, a gold metallic bra that only covers the sides of her breasts, and a gold metallic bikini bottom. Her arms and legs are charred black and glowing with bright blue flames.

Kama's [[kama (beast iii/l) (fate)|Beast III/L]] form borrows from this Ascension, but her coloration changes and she gains a set of horns depending on which Beast form she's in - either her "Kama/Mara":https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/fategrandorder/images/a/a1/KamaBeastHorn.png/revision/latest?cb=20210225145537 form, or her "Demon Lord of Lust":https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/fategrandorder/images/3/36/KamaBeast2.png/revision/latest?cb=20210225145551 form.

title: kama_(second_ascension)_(fate)

[[Kama (fate)|]] in her Second Ascension outfit from [[Fate/Grand Order]]. She is in her teenaged form here, with shoulder-length white hair and a pink bow tied on the left side of her head like [[Matou Sakura]]. She wears a purple halterneck top that becomes see-through around the abdomen, gold shoulder pads holding a series of purple strips, tight purple sleeves, a gold metallic bikini bottom, purple thighhighs, and gold high heels.

Note that her halterneck top is the same in her First Ascension. The best way to tell them apart is that the First Ascension outfit has the dark skirt beneath the top's sheer part, whereas the Second Ascension outfit has a gold metallic bikini bottom.

title: road_bicycle
body:
The term road bicycle is used to describe bicycles built for traveling at speed on paved roads. Some sources use the term to mean racing bicycle.

Compared to other styles of bicycle, road bicycles share common features:

* The tires are narrow, high-pressure (100 psi (700 kPa) or higher), and smooth to decrease rolling resistance
* The handlebars are bent ("dropped") to allow the rider position to be leaned forward and downward, which reduces the forward vertical cross sectional area and thus highly reduces the air resistance
* They usually use derailleur gears; however, single-speed and fixed-gear varieties exist
* They either use disc brakes or rim brakes (although there might be technical differences, for example road bike calliper brakes use shorter and wider pads than mountain bike cantilevers)
* The bicycle is of a lightweight construction

title: mountain_bicycle
body: A mountain bike (MTB) or mountain bicycle is a bicycle designed for off-road cycling. Mountain bikes share some similarities with other bicycles but incorporate features designed to enhance durability and performance in rough terrain, which makes them heavier, more complex, and less efficient on smooth surfaces.

title: star_conflict
body:
Star Conflict is a free-to-play dynamic massively multiplayer online space action game. The gaming platform Steam describes it as an "action-packed, massively multiplayer space simulation game". The core of the game is PvP spaceships battles, PvE (Co-Op) missions and an open world. The game uses a free-to-play business model.

Star Conflict has been developed by the Russian company Targem Games (StarGem department) and published by Gaijin Entertainment. The game started on February 1, 2012 and reached open beta test on July 24, 2012. It has been available on Steam since February 27, 2013. The release took place on September 4, 2014 (Version 1.0).

http://star-conflict.com/en/

h4. Spaceships

There are 4 basic [[spacecraft|ship]] classes: [[interseptor_(star_conflict)|interceptors]], [[fighter_(star_conflict)|fighters]], [[frigate]]s and [[destroyer]]s. They are fundamentally different in external view, size, control, speed, etc. Each class has a variety of different modules available, weapons and features, designed for certain tasks. These variations determine the role of the ship on the battlefield.

title: counter_watch_(counter:side)
body:
A device in the setting of the game [[Counter:Side]], worn by humans who have become [i]Counters[/i].

It resembles an ordinary watch, but Counter watches function differently. The watch behaves more like the "Doomsday Clock":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doomsday_Clock].
If the time "runs out", the Counter wearing the watch turns into a [i]Shadow[/i], the Counter-equivalent of a Corrupted Object (abbreviated as C.O. in-game).

To keep the watch from ticking down and raise the timer up, the counter must feed the device with a special rare element dubbed [i]Eternium[/i].

title: scp-166
body:
Subject of the [[SCP Foundation]]. Codenamed [b]Teenage Succubus[/b], she is a normal teenage girl who goes nude due to her very fragile skin. As her name suggests, she has an unusual power to cause any nearby male who looks at her to want to have sex with her, to the point of obsession, which she is unable to control. These incidents cause distress for her as she is a Catholic nun who leads a chaste life. As a result, she lives in a secluded place protected by an all female SCP staff.

[spoilers]Strongly implied, if not flat-out stated in some places, to be [[Alto Clef]]'s daughter.[/spoilers]

Following revision in 2020, she is now codenamed [b]Just a Teenage Gaea[/b].  She is now a young woman with the antlers, hooves, and tail of a reindeer.  She has the paranormal ability to revert any artificially-created material or structure within 15 meters to an unrefined 'natural' state; the more advanced the material or device the faster it degrades.  Simultaneously, she causes plant life to grow within the same radius, even without any soil or seeds.  She is unable to control these abilities, so has to wear basic organic cotton clothes and live in a specially made containment chamber.  She retains her history as a devout catholic nun.

title: ko~n
body:
An onomatopoeic fox noise, probably a growl.

It's somewhat common for fox characters to say something to this effect on occasion, and the word "konkon" (コンコン) is even a diminutive word for foxes, but perhaps no one uses it more iconically than [[touhou|Touhou Project's]] [[Kudamaki Tsukasa]], for whom it can be considered a catchphrase. This stems from the fact that one of her in-game portraits displays her saying こーん right before her battle, notably written in Hiragana rather than Katakana, the alphabet typically reserved for onomatopoeia. Many fan works show her saying this, and Akatsuki Records even made a music video based entirely around Tsukasa making ko~n puns named ""Ko~nsultant!":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RypOHapqCeQ]."

title: hms_nelson
body: A British WW2 [[battleship]] armed with 9 16" guns in three triple turrets and capable of making 23 knots. The nameship of the first class of treaty battleships, Nelson can be best summed up as a cut-down [[G3 battlecruiser]]; maintaining comparable firepower to G3s but being 8 knots slower, slightly less well armored, and good 12 000 tons lighter when at full displacement, thanks to being designed within the limits imposed on new capital ships by the Washington Naval Treaty. HMS Nelson was laid down 28th of December 1922, launched 3rd of September 1925, commissioned 15th of August 1927, and ultimately scrapped in Inverkeithing, Scotland, in 1949.

body:
A backscratcher (also known as a scratch-back or a back scratcher) is a tool used for relieving an itch in an area that cannot easily be reached just by one's own hands, typically the back.

They are generally long, slender, and rod-shaped, with a knob on one end for holding and a rake-like device, sometimes in the form of a human hand, on the other end to perform the actual scratching.  Some variants feature massage rollers or a massage ball on the end opposite from the rake.

body:
[[Kiyohime (fate)|]] in her Third Ascension form from [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Her hair turns white, her horns become black, and her eyes remain yellow. Some artists interpret her eyes to be red due to her "Servant Card illustration":https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/fategrandorder/images/6/6a/S056_Stage3.webp/revision/latest?cb=20210204144802, but her "in-game sprite":https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/fategrandorder/images/3/32/KiyohimeNewSprite3.png/revision/latest?cb=20190102102319 has her with yellow eyes. She wears a black kimono with a yellow bow at the back. Her folding fan is also opened in this ascension, showing a white snake in front of a fiery background.

If her skin, hair, and horns reflect this Ascension design even if she isn't wearing the outfit, this tag can be used to reference the visual change (post #3784080). [b]The only exception to this is [[kiyohime (swimsuit lancer) (third ascension) (fate)|Kiyohime Swimsuit Lancer's Third Ascension swimsuit]], which is treated as a wholly separate character from this one.[/b]

This gives the Reborns Gundam a resemblance to the [[Hi-Nu Gundam]] from [[Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children]] novel (though the obvious difference is their color scheme). title: larry_foulke
body:
Ustio Air Force
6th Air Division
66th Air Force Unit
Galm 2 Larry "Pixy" Foulke

"This man was his buddy. And his enemy." 
-Brett Thompson

Galm team's number 2, wingman to [[Cipher_(ace_combat)|]] was a [[F-15 Eagle]] mercenary fighter pilot during the Belkan War in [[Ace Combat Zero]]. Earned the nickname "Solo Wing" because he flew back and landed his aircraft at base with one wing after returning from a skirmish. Being proud of that feat, he had the right wing on his plane painted red. During the war, he defected and joined the coupe movement of "A World With No Boundaries" aligned with Belka, Osea, and Sapin; while another pilot from Crow Team transferred in as Galm 1's wingman. After narrowly escaping death in the final fight against his former ally over the skies of Avalon Dam, a badly wounded Pixy dragged his body to a nuclear detonation site on Belkan soil where he was saved by the people who lived there. Many years later, Larry would join [[ISAF]] and fight on the front lines in the second Usean Continental War in [[Ace Combat 04]] as a ground soldier. He is in search of a world without borders, hoping to find the true meaning behind them. 

Voiced by Yuri Lowenthal

“Every time I flew with him his skill stood out. He was unstoppable. It didn't matter where the battlefield was, the man had complete trust in his own powers. He was born for battle, a demon lord who struck down all opposition. He'd pay no heed to the troubles of those who flew with him. Before long, everyone had taken notice of him. More and more would show up to watch him go off on sortie. Mercenaries or maintenance crew, it didn't matter. People wanted to burn his image into their memories. Hell, they weren't the only ones."

-[[Larry Foulke]] 

"The Demon Lord of the Round Table. A warrior who soared through the Belkan War, inspired both fear, and admiration. His presence filled the skies for but a few short months before he disappeared. Apart from that, nothing is known about him. I was never able to find out what kind of person he really was. But whenever they talked about him, they always had a slight smile on their faces. That perhaps, may be my answer."

-Brett Thompson

title: yuubari_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
[[Yuubari (Kancolle)|]]'s K2 form (post #3748023).

In her second remodels, released 14 January 2020, she gains the ability to equip five pieces of equipment but loses the ability to equip secondary guns. In addition, she has equipment restrictions on what kind can be carried on the last two slots (no main guns and torpedoes on fourth slot, fifth slot can only accommodate small radars and AA guns).

Her kai ni form turns her into an AA cruiser a la [[Isuzu (Kancolle)|]], sharing an AA cut-in equipment setup as [[Kasumi Kai Ni (Kancolle)|]].

In kai ni [i]Toku[/i], she is geared as a minisub mothership/transport cruiser that can carry minisubs (for opening torpedo attacks), landing craft, and amphibious tanks, but loses the ability to equip large radars and reduces her speed.

Her kai ni D form is geared as an anti-submarine cruiser but retains the restrictions of Kai Ni Toku.

In all forms, the most defining difference from her base form is that her rig is now modified to match the real-life Yuubari, while she switches her [[hair ribbon]] color to [[white ribbon|white]] ([i]the most obvious change if she's not depicted with her battle rig[/i]).

title: aim-7_sparrow
body:
The AIM-7 Sparrow (Air Intercept [[Missile]]) is an American, medium-range semi-active radar homing air-to-air [[missile]] operated by the [[United States Air Force]], [[United States Navy]], and United States Marine Corps, as well as other various air forces and navies. Sparrow and its derivatives were the West's principal beyond visual range (BVR) air-to-air [[missile]] from the late 1950s until the 1990s. It remains in service, although it is being phased out in aviation applications in favor of the more advanced AIM-120 AMRAAM.

The early Sparrow was intended primarily for use against larger targets, especially bombers and had numerous operational limitations in other uses. Against smaller targets, the need to receive a strong reflected radar signal made achieving lock-on at the [[missile]]'s effective range difficult. As the launching [[aircraft]]'s own radar needed to be pointed at the target throughout the engagement, this meant that in fighter-vs-fighter combat, the enemy fighter would often approach within the range of shorter-range infrared homing missiles while the launching aircraft had to continue flying towards its target. Additionally, early models were only effective against targets at roughly the same or higher altitudes, below which reflections from the ground became a problem.

A number of upgraded Sparrow designs were developed to address these issues. In the early 1970s, the [[royal_air_force|RAF]] developed a version with an inverse monopulse seeker and improved motor known as Skyflash, while the Italian Air Force introduced the similar Aspide. Both had the ability to be fired at targets below the launching fighter ("look-down, shoot down"), were more resistant to countermeasures, and were much more accurate in the terminal phase. This basic concept was then made part of the US Sparrows in the M model (for monopulse) and some of these were later updated as the P model, the last to be produced in the US. Aspides sold to [[China]] resulted in the locally produced PL10. The [[japan_self-defense_force|Japan Self-Defense Forces]] also employ the Sparrow missile, though it is being phased out and replaced by the Mitsubishi AAM-4.

h4. External links
